<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">

<!-- @pageTitle = About -->

<!-- @include "global/head.kit"-->

<body id="about-page">
    <!-- @include "global/header_nav.kit" -->

    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="content margins">
                <!-- Whatever we're doing for the page title -->
                <div class="repeated-container breakpoint-md">
                    <h3 class="repeated-text">Creativity can strike at any moment and the best ideas are scribbled on a dirty napkin.</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="team-pic-container">
                    <picture>
                        <source
                        media="(min-width: 768px)"
                        srcset="https://placehold.co/634x470.png" />
                        <img src="https://placehold.co/272x354.png" alt="DN team pic"/>
                    </picture>
                    <div id="about-square-1" class="squares squares-sm"></div>
                </div>
                <div id="about-square-2" class="squares squares-sm"></div>
                <div id="about-square-3" class="squares squares-sm"></div>
                <div id="about-square-4" class="squares squares-sm"></div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="story">
            <!-- wtf do i do here -->
            <div class="story-grid"></div>
            <div class="story-text margins">
                <p class="button-text">When you share your story</p>
                <p>with another person, you are inviting them into your world, and in doing so, you build a larger community of people with shared worlds. That perspective is what creates connection– with individuals and with brands.</p>
                <p class="paragraph-spacing">When we first started Dirty Napkin in 2023, we hardly knew the difference between a font and a color. We genuinely thought that Comic Sans and blue were the same thing. Despite inexperience, we were eager and wanted to expand our design skills to the real world. Fast forward to modern day and we are a well-oiled machine.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="what-we-do">
            <div class="content">
                <div class="whatwedo-bkgd-grid"></div>
                <h3>At its core, Dirty Napkin is a two-pronged entity:</h3>
                <div class="mobile-squares-container">
                    <div class="square"></div>
                    <div class="square"></div>
                    <div class="square"></div>
                </div>
                <p>If you are currently pursuing your passion, we can design awesome graphics for you that boldly communicate who you are and draw in like-minded people.</p>
                <p>If you haven’t yet started, let us be the inspiration. If a small team of 4 can create something that alters your world, you can do it too.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="bios-conc margins">
            <div class="bios">
                <div class="bio">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/272x272.png" alt="Evan headshot">
                    <div class="bio-text">
                        <h4>Evan Whitaker</h4>
                        <p>is our Designer and Brand Strategist. He is a figment of our imagination.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bio">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/272x272.png" alt="Dan headshot">
                    <div class="bio-text">
                        <h4>Dan Soslowsky</h4>
                        <p>is our Designer and Project Manager. He is not afraid of the dark, but of what lurks within it.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bio">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/272x272.png" alt="Noah headshot">
                    <div class="bio-text">
                        <h4>Noah Simon</h4>
                        <p>is our Designer and Resource Manager. He believes a hotdog is not a sandwich, but neither is a grilled cheese</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bio">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/272x272.png" alt="Nick headshot">
                    <div class="bio-text">
                        <h4>Nicholas Evangelinos</h4>
                        <p>is our Designer and Company Strategist. He is responsible for every major financial crash since 2005.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- @include "global/footer.kit" -->

    </main>
    <!-- @import "global/scripts.kit"-->
</body>

</html>